<concept xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" id="generic-topic" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="urn:oasis:names:tc:dita:xsd:concept.xsd:1.1">
  <title>Generic Topic</title>
  <conbody>
    <p id="topic-definition"><term>Generic topics</term><indexterm>DITA generic topic</indexterm> are  unspecialized single-subject articles. The generic topic provides the base for other <xref href="dita-specialization-serna-free.xml">specialized</xref> topic types (e.g. task, concept), and also lets you author content that does not belong in existing specialized types.</p>
    <p>You can find more information about the generic topic type at: <xref href="http://docs.oasis-open.org/dita/v1.1/OS/archspec/generictopics.html" format="html"/>.</p>
  </conbody>
